        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; the opposite, positive view of life. The words for ‘food’ and ‘raiment’ are both unused in N.T. except here; both are in the plural, indicating ‘supplies of,’ for each mouth to be fed, each household to be clothed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
