            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "raiment",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] A rather out-of-the-way word for ‘clothing,’ if we go by the use found once in Aristotle and once in Josephus, Ar. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Pol",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". vii. 17; Jos. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "B. J",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ii. 8. 5: literally, ‘covering;’ and so R.V., perhaps merely to keep an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unusualness",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of phrase. But the meaning ‘shelter,’ tent or roof-covering, has been also assigned, from the root word having a more common turn towards this; and ‘covering’ may have been chosen to include this, if not to express it alone. But the immediate context in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "1 Timothy 6:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Timothy 6:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " favours the reference to merely ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "personal",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " possessions such as dress.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "let us be therewith content",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The verb is future passive, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "we shall be therewith content",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as R.V.; hardly an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "implied",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " exhortation, but ‘we shall, if we are godly.’ This rendering is preferable to that in the margin of R.V. ‘in these we shall have enough’ from the similar use of the passive, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 3:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘be content with your wages;’ ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 13:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ‘content with such things as ye have.’ The connexion of the word with ‘contentment’ above should also be maintained.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
