        "text": "N.T.o.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Raiment (σκεπάσματα)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "N.T.o. olxx. It means covering generally, though the reference is probably to clothing. von Soden aptly remarks that a dwelling is not a question of life with an Oriental.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let us be content (ἀρκεσθησόμεθα)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "More correctly, we shall be content. Once in Paul, 2 Corinthians 12:9. A few times in lxx. Comp. Ps. of Sol. 16:12: \"But with good will and cheerfulness uphold thou my soul; when thou strengthenest my soul I shall be satisfied (ἀρκέσει μοι) with what thou givest me.\" ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "More correctly, we shall be content. Once in Paul, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Corinthians 12:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". A few times in lxx. Comp. Ps. of Sol. 16:12: \"But with good will and cheerfulness uphold thou my soul; when thou strengthenest my soul I shall be satisfied (ἀρκέσει μοι) with what thou givest me.\" ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
